        <article>
            <h1><u>Pokemon</u></h1>
            <p>Pokémon is one of the most famous anime series in the world. It follows the journey of a young trainer named <strong>Ash Ketchum</strong> and his loyal Pokémon <strong>Pikachu</strong>. Together, they travel across different regions, meet new friends, catch powerful Pokémon, and battle gym leaders to become the greatest Pokémon Master.</p>
        </article>

        <section>
            <h2>Regions Explored by Ash Ketchum</h2>
            <p>In his journey to become a Pokémon Master, Ash Ketchum traveled across many official regions of the Pokémon world, each filled with new adventures, Pokémon species, and unique challenges.</p>
            <aside>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Kanto</strong> – The starting region where Ash began his journey with Pikachu.</li>
                    <li><strong>Johto</strong> – Home to many new Pokémon from Generation II and the Johto League.</li>
                    <li><strong>Hoenn</strong> – A region filled with water routes, volcanoes, and contests.</li>
                    <li><strong>Sinnoh</strong> – A snowy region with ancient legends and the powerful Pokémon Dialga and Palkia.</li>
                    <li><strong>Unova</strong> – A modern and diverse region based on New York, with brand-new Pokémon.</li>
                    <li><strong>Kalos</strong> – A beautiful region inspired by France, known for Mega Evolutions.</li>
                    <li><strong>Alola</strong> – A tropical region based on Hawaii, where Ash attended Pokémon School.</li>
                    <li><strong>Galar</strong> – A region inspired by the UK, where Ash participated in the World Coronation Series.</li>
                    <li><strong>Paldea</strong> – The latest region introduced in the Pokémon Scarlet and Violet series, inspired by Spain.</li>
                </ol>
            </aside>

